% Automatisch generiert — Thema: Abortion
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro29).  % [pro] The World Health Organization estimated in 2004 that unsafe abortions cause 68,000 maternal deaths worldwide each year.
arg(pro29b).  % [pro] Many of those maternal deaths occur in developing countries where safe and legal abortion services are difficult to access.
arg(pro7).  % [pro] If the State is interested in protecting fetal life after viability, the State may proscribe abortion after viability, except when it is necessary to preserve the life or health of the mother.
arg(pro71).  % [pro] Americans are more accepting of abortions that occur early in pregnancy when the fetus is not as developed and is not viable (able to survive on its own outside of the woman's body).
arg(pro63).  % [pro] Not all abortions are unjustified according to this argument.
arg(pro63b).  % [pro] Abortion would be justified if the same justification could be applied to killing an adult human.
arg(pro58).  % [pro] Abortion reduces crime.
arg(pro36).  % [pro] The National Cancer Institute (NCI), the American Cancer Society (ACS), and the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists all refuted the claim that abortion can lead to a higher probability of developing breast cancer.
arg(pro27).  % [pro] The court also ruled that the word "person" in the Constitution did not include a fetus.
arg(con140).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton led the fight for women's right to own property, to vote, and to obtain equal education.
arg(con140b).  % [con] Susan B. Anthony and Elizabeth Cady Stanton spoke out against abortion.
arg(con23).  % [con] I will always support legislation that would end abortion.
arg(con23b).  % [con] I will always support legislation that would lead society in the direction of ending abortion.
arg(con152).  % [con] For this reason, I introduced S. 583, the Life at Conception Act on March 14, 2013.
arg(con109).  % [con] Half of all women having abortions each year have had at least one previous abortion, according to the Guttmacher Institute.
arg(con109b).  % [con] 8.5 % of abortions reported to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in 2010 were performed by women who had three or more previous abortions.
arg(con8).  % [con] Fetuses feel pain during the abortion procedure.
arg(con24).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report overwhelming guilt.
arg(con24b).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report experiencing nightmares.
arg(con24c).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report excessive drinking.
arg(con24d).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report drug abuse.
arg(con24e).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report increased promiscuity.
arg(con24f).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report an inability to form or maintain relationships.
arg(con24g).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report difficulty bonding with later children.
arg(con24h).  % [con] Women who have had abortions report other ways in which they are suffering.

