att(pro29, pro7).  % [NONE] conf=70 — Data on deaths from unsafe abortions challenges the premise that restricting abortion after viability is acceptable, as it may increase unsafe procedures.
att(pro29, con23).  % [NONE] conf=65 — Evidence of deaths from unsafe abortions undermines the premise that ending abortion is beneficial, suggesting it could increase mortality.
att(con23, pro29b).  % [NONE] conf=70 — B's commitment to end abortion contradicts A's implication that legal abortion reduces maternal deaths
att(con23b, pro29b).  % [NONE] conf=70 — B's support for moving society toward ending abortion opposes A's implied policy benefit
att(con152, pro29b).  % [NONE] conf=75 — B introduces anti‑abortion legislation, directly opposing A's claim that lack of legal abortion causes deaths
att(pro63b, pro7).  % [NONE] conf=70 — Pro63b challenges the moral distinction used by pro7 by suggesting the same justification would also permit killing an adult, undermining pro7's premise.
att(con24, pro7).  % [NONE] conf=70 — The claim that women experience overwhelming guilt suggests mental‑health harms, undermining the premise that only physical life/health exceptions justify post‑viability bans.
att(con24b, pro7).  % [NONE] conf=70 — Reporting nightmares indicates psychological injury, challenging the premise that only physical health matters for post‑viability abortion restrictions.
att(pro63b, pro71).  % [NONE] conf=80 — Equating abortion’s justification with that for killing an adult exposes a moral inconsistency, challenging the acceptance of early abortions based on viability.
att(pro27, pro7).  % [NONE] conf=80 — The constitutional ruling that a fetus is not a "person" undermines the premise that the State can protect fetal life after viability.
att(con140b, pro71).  % [NONE] conf=70 — The claim that early suffragists opposed abortion challenges the premise that early abortion is broadly accepted and morally justified.
att(con152, pro71).  % [NONE] conf=75 — Introducing a Life‑at‑Conception Act asserts that abortion is impermissible, directly opposing the claim that early abortions are socially accepted.
att(con8, pro71).  % [NONE] conf=70 — If fetuses feel pain during early abortions, the claim that early abortions are more acceptable because the fetus is undeveloped is undermined.
